article.description: Ta'Shia Phillips had 14 points and 11 rebounds and April Phillips had 12 points and 12 rebounds to lift Xavier (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) past Akron 69-44 on Friday night.
article.headline: Ta'Shia, April Phillips give Xavier edge in rout of Akron
article.linkText: Phillips duo helps No. 21 Xavier overpower Akron
article.story:
CINCINNATI -- Ta'Shia Phillips had 14 points and 11 rebounds and April Phillips had 12 points and 12 rebounds to lift Xavier (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) past Akron 69-44 on Friday night.

Xavier earned its fifth consecutive victory overall and fifth straight over the Zips.

Xavier (7-2) built the lead by stopping Akron's perimeter shooters in the first half. The Zips made just 6-of-30 first-half shots, and they were held scoreless for nearly six minutes as Xavier surged to a 27-10 lead.

Akron (2-5) got no closer than 15 points for the rest of the game.

Xavier used depth and balance to seal the win as 11 players scored for the Musketeers.

Xavier's past four wins have been by at least 20 points.
